
TOPIC: MAP/SIZEP0

53256          D008          SIZEP0

(W) Size of player 0. POKE with zero
or two for normal size (eight color
clocks wide), POKE with one to double
a player's width (sixteen color clocks
wide), and POKE with three for
quadruple width (32 color clocks
wide). Each player can have its own
width set.  A normal size player might
look something like this:

00011000
00111100
01111110
11111111
11111111
01111110
00111100
00011000

In double width, the same player would
like this:

0000001111000000
0000111111110000
0011111111111100
0011111111111100
0000111111110000
0000001111000000

In quadruple width, the same player
would become:

00000000000011111111000000000000
00000000111111111111111100000000
00001111111111111111111111110000
11111111111111111111111111111111
11111111111111111111111111111111
00001111111111111111111111110000
00000000111111111111111100000000
00000000000011111111000000000000

Bit use is:
                              COLOR
Bit 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0   SIZE   CLOCKS
    ..unused... 0 0   Normal      8
                0 1   Double     16
                1 0   Normal      8
                1 1   Quadruple  32

              M0PL

(R) Missile 0 to player collisions.
There is no missile-to-missile
collision register. Bit use is:

Bit      7  6  5  4  3  2  1  0
Player   ..unused..  3  2  1  0
Decimal  ..........  8  4  2  1

